<h1>Coding challenge: Average Bases!</h1>

<div class="row justify-content-between">
    <div class="col-md-5 border-1">
        <h3>Hackathon value: 6</h3>
        <h3>Description</h3>
        <p>
            The number 123, when expressed in base 16, consists of two digits:
            7 (base 10) and 11 (base 10). The sum of these two digits is 18 (in base 10). 
            Given an input number <span class="code highlighted">num</span>, find the average value of the sum of all the
            digits when expressing num in every number base from 2 to <span class="code highlighted">(num - 1)</span>.
        </p>

        <p>
            Given an integer input <span class="code highlighted">num</span>, 
            find the average sum of digits that number would have in every
            number base from 2 to <span class="code highlighted">(num - 1)</span>. 
        </p>

        <h3>Limits</h3>
        <p>
            <span class="code">3 &lt;= num &lt;= 1000</span>
        </p>

        <h3>Examples</h3>
        <p>
            <span class="code">5 =&gt; "7/3"</span>
            <br />
            Explanation: 5 converts to "101" in base 2, "12" in base 3, and "11" in base 4.  Result: ((1 + 0 + 1) + (1 + 2) + (1 + 1)) / 3.
        </p>
        <p>
            <span class="code">22 =&gt; "113/20"</span>
            <br />
            Explanation:
            <br />
            base 2: "10110" => sum: 3
            <br />
            base 3: "211" => sum: 4
            <br />
            base 4: "112" => sum: 4
            <br />
            base 5: "42" => sum: 6
            <br />
            ...
            <br />
            base 12: "1_10" => sum: 11
            <br />
            ...
            <br />
            base 21: "11" => sum: 2
            <br />
            Total sums: 113, 20 bases.  Return "113/20".
        </p>
        <p>
            <span class="code">14 =&gt; "17/4"</span>
            <br />
            Explanation: 51 total sum, 12 bases.  The fraction "51/12" reduces to "17/4".  Return "17/4".
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-5 border-1">
        <div class="mb-3">
            <h2>Your code:</h2>
            <form id="code-form" method="post" asp-controller="CodeProblems" asp-action="AverageBases">
                <textarea id="code" name="code" style="width: 100%;font-family: monospace;">static string AverageBases(int num) {}</textarea>
                <input type="submit" value="Submit" />
            </form>
        </div>
        <div id="response-container">
            <partial name="_CodeResponsePartial" model="null" />
        </div>
    </div>
</div>